SIMPLE: moribund
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moribund
<hw>Mor"i*bund</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>moribundus</ets>, from <ets>moriri</ets> to die. See
<er>Mortal</er>.]</ety> <def>In a dying state; dying; at the point of
death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The patient was comatose and <qex>moribund</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Copland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moribund</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moribund
<hw>Mor"i*bund</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dying
person.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moric</ent>⟦br⟧
